WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:04.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And in the day's
other news: The Supreme Court
also announced that it will

00:04.733 --> 00:08.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
decide a case pitting gay
rights against religion.

00:08.200 --> 00:13.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At issue is whether
a Denver baker acted
legally when he refused
to sell a same-sex couple

00:14.433 --> 00:15.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a wedding cake.

00:15.666 --> 00:18.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He cited his religious beliefs.

00:18.066 --> 00:22.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In another case, the
justices ruled 7-2 that a
church-run school in Missouri
may seek taxpayer-funded

00:24.666 --> 00:27.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
grants for a new playground.

00:27.466 --> 00:32.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump has again
accused former President
Obama of failing to stop
Russian interference

00:33.533 --> 00:35.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the 2016 election.

00:35.666 --> 00:40.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Twitter today, he charged:
"The reason that President
Obama did nothing is that he

00:41.866 --> 00:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
expected Hillary
Clinton would win.

00:43.233 --> 00:44.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He didn't choke.

00:44.333 --> 00:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He colluded or obstructed."

00:46.800 --> 00:51.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump insisted
investigators have no
evidence that his campaign
aides colluded with Russia.

00:53.633 --> 00:57.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
British Prime Minister Theresa
May struck a deal with a
Northern Ireland party today

00:59.033 --> 01:00.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to bolster her
minority government.

01:00.800 --> 01:04.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
May's Conservatives
lost their majority in
this month's election.

01:04.433 --> 01:09.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now they have agreed to provide
some $1.3 billion in extra
funding to Northern Ireland.

01:11.366 --> 01:15.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's in return for the
Democratic Unionist Party's
10 votes in Parliament.

01:17.100 --> 01:20.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
British officials now say that
75 high-rise buildings tested
for fire safety, have failed.

01:22.133 --> 01:25.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The testing began after
London's Grenfell Tower fire.

01:25.400 --> 01:29.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The siding on that building
may have fueled the blaze.

01:29.933 --> 01:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The other buildings tested so
far are all over the country.

01:33.400 --> 01:37.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is not clear how long it
will take to fix the problem.

01:37.233 --> 01:42.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In China: Nobel peace laureate
Liu Xiaobo has been released
from prison to a hospital

01:43.866 --> 01:47.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
after being diagnosed with
late-stage liver cancer.

01:47.233 --> 01:50.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Liu has been a leading
dissident for decades.

01:50.333 --> 01:55.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2009, he was sentenced
to 11 years on a charge
of inciting subversion.

01:56.733 --> 01:59.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But his lawyer says that
today's release means little.

01:59.000 --> 02:02.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MO SHAOPING, Attorney for Liu
Xiaobo (through translator):
In principle, he will not be

02:02.266 --> 02:06.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
allowed to see guests, or
visitors, because of the
special nature of his case.

02:06.066 --> 02:11.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Under medical parole, a
person is still serving a
term while being treated
in a medical facility,

02:11.933 --> 02:13.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
even if it's outside of prison.

02:13.066 --> 02:14.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Liu Xiaobo's case is special.

02:14.733 --> 02:17.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't think the authorities
will allow him to have visitors.

02:17.666 --> 02:22.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Liu won the
Nobel Peace Prize in 2010 for
his efforts demanding greater

02:24.100 --> 02:27.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
political freedoms and an end
to one-party rule in China.

02:27.900 --> 02:32.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back in this country, the
family of Philando Castile has
reached a $3 million settlement

02:34.333 --> 02:37.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
over his fatal shooting by
a Minnesota police officer.

02:37.133 --> 02:41.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Castile, a black man, was killed
during a traffic stop last year.

02:41.466 --> 02:46.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The officer was acquitted
this month of manslaughter
before being fired by
the city of St. Anthony.

02:48.466 --> 02:53.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Takata Corporation has filed
for bankruptcy protection over
faulty air bag inflators linked

02:54.133 --> 02:57.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to at least 16 deaths worldwide.

02:57.100 --> 03:02.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The company faces tens
of billions of dollars
in costs and liabilities
stemming from recalls

03:02.700 --> 03:04.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and lawsuits.

03:04.766 --> 03:08.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The filings today in the U.S.
and Japan clear the way for a
rival company to take over most

03:10.200 --> 03:12.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Takata's assets.

03:12.333 --> 03:17.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On Wall Street today, the Dow
Jones industrial average gained
14 points to close at 21409.

03:18.766 --> 03:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell 18, and the
S&amp;P 500 added a fraction.
